		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Todays trip : PPU H/V counter.<br /><br />Overview, showing its location:<br /><img src="http://ogamespec.com/imgstore/whc502e5d7e22238.jpg" alt="Image" /><br /><br />Transistor-level circuit. Still not sure where is &quot;H&quot; and where is &quot;V&quot; <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /> ( have feeling that V-scanline counter is on the left side)<br /><img src="http://ogamespec.com/imgstore/whc502e5d83b0d9d.jpg" alt="Image" /><br />(high quality image and LSD cover in attachments)<br /><br />H/V counter is driven by pixel clock (PCLK).<br /><br />This is my last public domain work, since I decided to keep competition amongst NES emulators  <img src="./images/smilies/icon_mrgreen.gif" alt=":mrgreen:" title="Mr. Green" /><br />I will release whole stuff, when my own emu will be ready )<br /><br />Enjoy !

		
